main event: Two unidentified objects were observed in the sky over Klamath Falls, Oregon on March 14, 1955.
interesting points: The first object was described as star-like and very bright, with a long observation duration.
The second object was described as meteor-like, flying from south to north.
The objects were evaluated as possibly astronomical, with the first object identified as the planet Jupiter and the second as a meteor.
The report was classified as a Project 10073 Record Card.
sighted object: Two unidentified objects, one star-like and bright, the other meteor-like
